Start
/ Strict without a kind → no byte probe runs (nothing to check against);
/ builds clean. Soft-degradation contract: strict implies "match what was
/ asked", and nothing was asked for kind.
- set %x% = "irrelevant" as image strict
- assert %x.Type.Name% equals "image"
- assert %x.Type.Kind% is null
- assert %x.Type.Strict% equals true
